@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "HTTP Protocol - Part 1";
}

<body data-topic="web-communication-http1">
<div class="container">
    <h1 class="text-center">HTTP Protocol - Part 1: The Language of the Web</h1>

    <div class="beginner-note">
        <div class="beginner-note-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="beginner-note-content">
            <h4>Think of HTTP Like a Restaurant Conversation</h4>
            <p><strong>HTTP = The rules for how clients and servers talk</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Simple analogy:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Customer (Client) speaks in a specific way: "I'd like a pizza, please"</li>
                <li>Server understands this format and replies: "One pizza coming up!"</li>
                <li>Both follow the same conversation rules</li>
                <li>Without these rules, they couldn't understand each other</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>In web terms:</strong> HTTP is the standard language all web devices use to communicate!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
        <p><strong>HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol)</strong> is the set of rules that governs how clients and servers communicate on the web. Every single web page you visit uses HTTP!</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Quick Definition:</strong> HTTP is <strong>the official language of the web</strong> - it's how browsers and servers talk to each other.
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">HTTP Basics: Requests and Responses</h2>
    
    <div class="http-flow">
        <div class="flow-step client-step">
            <div class="flow-icon">
                <i class="fas fa-laptop"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-content">
                <h5>Client Sends Request</h5>
                <p>"Please give me facebook.com"</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flow-arrow">
            <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="flow-icon">
                <i class="fas fa-exchange-alt"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-content">
                <h5>HTTP Protocol</h5>
                <p>Standard format for communication</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flow-arrow">
            <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flow-step server-step">
            <div class="flow-icon">
                <i class="fas fa-server"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="flow-content">
                <h5>Server Sends Response</h5>
                <p>"Here's the Facebook homepage"</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">HTTP Request: Breaking It Down</h2>
    
    <div class="http-request-demo">
        <div class="request-header">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-paper-plane"></i> What Your Browser Actually Sends</h4>
        </div>
        
        <div class="request-content">
            <div class="request-line">
                <span class="method">GET</span>
                <span class="path">/homepage</span>
                <span class="version">HTTP/1.1</span>
            </div>
            
            <div class="request-headers">
                <div class="header-line">
                    <span class="header-name">Host:</span>
                    <span class="header-value">www.facebook.com</span>
                </div>
                <div class="header-line">
                    <span class="header-name">User-Agent:</span>
                    <span class="header-value">Chrome/Windows</span>
                </div>
                <div class="header-line">
                    <span class="header-name">Accept:</span>
                    <span class="header-value">text/html,application/json</span>
                </div>
                <div class="header-line">
                    <span class="header-name">Accept-Language:</span>
                    <span class="header-value">en-US</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="request-body">
                <span class="empty-line">(Blank line - request ends here)</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="request-explanation">
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-badge">GET</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Method:</strong> What you want to do (GET means "get information")
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-badge">/homepage</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Path:</strong> What you want (Facebook's homepage)
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-badge">Host:</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Destination:</strong> Which server you're talking to
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-item">
                <div class="explanation-badge">User-Agent:</div>
                <div class="explanation-text">
                    <strong>Identifier:</strong> What browser/device you're using
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">HTTP Methods: Different Types of Requests</h2>
    
    <div class="http-methods">
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon get">
                <i class="fas fa-download"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>GET</h4>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Retrieve information</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Loading a webpage</p>
            <p><strong>Like saying:</strong> "Can I have that, please?"</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon post">
                <i class="fas fa-upload"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>POST</h4>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Send information</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Submitting a login form</p>
            <p><strong>Like saying:</strong> "Here's my information"</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon put">
                <i class="fas fa-edit"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>PUT</h4>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Update information</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Updating your profile</p>
            <p><strong>Like saying:</strong> "Please update this"</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon delete">
                <i class="fas fa-trash"></i>
            </div>
            <h4>DELETE</h4>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Remove information</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Deleting a post</p>
            <p><strong>Like saying:</strong> "Please remove this"</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="http-vs-https">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> HTTP vs HTTPS: What's the Difference?</h3>
        
        <div class="comparison">
            <div class="http-version">
                <div class="version-header http">
                    <h4>HTTP</h4>
                    <div class="security-badge insecure">Not Secure</div>
                </div>
                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-times text-danger"></i> Data sent in plain text</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-times text-danger"></i> Anyone can read it</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-times text-danger"></i> Like sending a postcard</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-globe"></i> Uses port 80</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="vs">
                <div class="vs-text">VS</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="http-version">
                <div class="version-header https">
                    <h4>HTTPS</h4>
                    <div class="security-badge secure">Secure</div>
                </div>
                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i> Data encrypted</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i> Only recipient can read</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i> Like sending a sealed letter</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Uses port 443</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="security-tip">
            <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i>
            <strong>Always look for the lock icon</strong> and "https://" in the address bar when entering sensitive information!
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="interactive-example">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-code"></i> Try It: Identify HTTP Methods</h3>
        
        <div class="scenario">
            <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> You're updating your Facebook profile</p>
            <div class="options">
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="false">GET - Getting your current profile</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="true">PUT - Updating your profile information</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="false">DELETE - Removing your profile</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="false">POST - Creating a new profile</button>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="scenario">
            <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> You search for "cute cat videos" on YouTube</p>
            <div class="options">
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="true">GET - Requesting search results</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="false">POST - Sending cat video data</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="false">PUT - Updating search results</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary option-btn" data-correct="false">DELETE - Removing videos</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="key-points">
        <h3>Key Points to Remember - Part 1</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>HTTP = Web Language</strong> - Rules for client-server communication</li>
            <li><strong>Requests & Responses</strong> - Clients ask, servers answer</li>
            <li><strong>HTTP Methods:</strong> GET (get data), POST (send data), PUT (update), DELETE (remove)</li>
            <li><strong>HTTPS is Secure HTTP</strong> - Encrypted for safety</li>
            <li><strong>Standard Format</strong> - All web devices understand HTTP</li>
            <li><strong>Stateless</strong> - Each request is independent (more on this in Part 2)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("Browser", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-outline-primary ajax-link">← What is a Browser?</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("HttpPart2", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-primary ajax-link">Continue: HTTP Part 2 →</a>
    </div>
</div>

